  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6658",
  "title": "refinementList/refine function call filters the wrong index",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nI have this SearchResult component that contain 2 InstantSearch and 2 indexes (for another reason, I cant make it to use 1 InstantSearch and 2 indexes)\n```\n<InstantSearch indexName=\"products\">\n   <CustomRefinementList attribute=\"categories\">\n</InstantSearch>\n<InstantSearch indexName=\"pages\">\n  <CustomRefinementList attribute=\"tags\">\n</InstantSearch>\n ```\n\nIn refinementList, there are keywords that being shared for both attributes e.g. `kitchen`.\n\n**the issue is** when I call `refine(\"kitchen\")` in `tags` refinementList. it filters `products` uiState instead of `pages` uiState.\n\nfor keyword that not being shared on both attributes, they work fine.\n\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nsee above.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/async-glade-5bcp0b\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nwhen I call `refine(\"kitchen\")` in `tags` refinementList. it should filter `pages` uiState.\n\n### Package version\n\n\"react-instantsearch\": \"^7.16.0\"\n\n### Operating system\n\nmacOS 15.5\n\n### Browser\n\nArc 1.99\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
